Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.21,0:00:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We're ready to explain the difference between causality and creation.\NWe're going to go back to the beginning of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.83,0:00:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We have quite a project for this afternoon, don't we? Explain existence\Nand how this all came about. If you go back to the levels of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.79,0:00:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,which anybody here can do through simple meditation, you will see that there are\Nvarious levels. Reality starts out at its highest level as the what Krishna would call the supreme
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.62,0:01:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,spirit. The Buddha would call the void. Christianity would call Godhead. This is\Nthe level of the unmanifest. The level of the unmanifest appears as nothingness
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.18,0:01:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,actually. It is allness. It is actually no thingness, however. It has the capacity to become\Nanything. All right, so the unmanifest is the infinite potentiality of divinity beyond form.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.23,0:02:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Advanced theoretical physics states that in one cubic centimeter of empty space, the potential\Ncentimeter of empty space is equivalent to greater than the total mass of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.53,0:02:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The universe, as you're aware, is expanding at the speed of light. As it expands at the\Nspeed of light, the infinite potential energy within that cubic centimeter of space also
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.68,0:02:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,expands at an infinite rate. Consequently, the infinite potentiality always balances\Nthe manifest. Out of that which is unmanifest, and it says in Genesis, in the beginning there
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.08,0:02:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,was the void, no thingness, arises awareness, arises consciousness, and consciousness is\Nthe beginning of the patterning of form. So the manifest is the outcome from the unmanifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.90,0:03:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So how does reality arise? The unmanifest becomes manifest.\NAnd it does so by virtue not of causality, but of creation. So there's a great leap in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.94,0:03:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,awareness here at this level of consciousness. Nothing within the manifest universe has intrinsic\Npower. Nothing in this universe can create its own existence. No rock can will itself
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.38,0:03:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,into being a rock.\NSo we would say, the primordial, the unmanifest, is the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.82,0:03:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So we would say the primordial, the unmanifest, is the universe.\NSo we would say the primordial, the unmanifest, is the universe. So we would say the primordial,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.08,0:03:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,intrinsic, basic, initial action, if you will, of the unmanifest, the supreme beingness of the\Nuniverse, was to move from unmanifest to manifest. As it does, if you meditate yourself, let's go
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.03,0:04:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,back in the other direction. We went from the unmanifest to the manifest domain, down to the\Nlevels of consciousness, going through awareness, consciousness itself, the witness, the observer,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.71,0:04:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the experiencer. Let's go back in the other direction, as you would in meditation. In\Nmeditation, you notice that thoughts are going through the mind, sensations through the physical
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.03,0:04:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,body, and with a little bit of observation, you will see that you are not the thoughts. The\Nthoughts come and go, but the you remains the same. You'll notice the same thing about the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.36,0:04:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,body. If the body has sensation, parts of the body may come and go, but the you is\Nthere.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.10,0:04:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The body is still the same. If we amputate one leg, the guy still says, I'm me. If we amputate the\Nother leg, he's still me. If we take off two arms, he still says, I'm me. So the I-ness, that which is
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.61,0:05:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I, then, is obviously not the physical body, or it would actually diminish as we chop off arms and\Nlegs. I lost a thumb one time. I went bye-bye. It's waiting for me in heaven. Bye-bye. And I still
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.92,0:05:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,felt like,\Nme. So me minus the thumb, I just felt like me. So me was really unaffected. The sense of I-ness,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.46,0:05:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,then, does not reside within the physical body. When you go to see somebody in there asleep, you\Nleave and you say, well, he wasn't there. Did you see Joe? No, he was asleep. So obviously, Joe is
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.00,0:05:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,not his body, because you saw Joe's body lying there. If Joe was his body, you'd say, yeah, I\Nsaw Joe. You'd say, no, I didn't see Joe. He was sleeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.35,0:05:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So obviously, you're not your body, that which is you, that which is I, the self, is not the body.\NNow, the mind is also a very transitory thing. So if you just close your eyes and witness what
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.64,0:06:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,goes on in meditation, you're aware that these thoughts, like fish, are going through the water.\NYou observe now that something is observing the fish. So beyond the content of the ego is the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.03,0:06:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,observer. How do you know what's going on in your thoughts? How do you know what they are?\NIt's only because there's an observer there and there's an experiencer. So there's that which
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.28,0:06:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is the self manifesting as the observer, the witness. And beyond that is the watcher. The\Nwatcher watches all this. And the watcher is unaffected by what it watches. So you might say
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.24,0:06:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness is impersonal. To become enlightened, you have to get rid of the thought that there's a\Npersonal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.70,0:06:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a separate thing called I that's unique in the universe.\NWhat's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.84,0:07:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If you just meditate for a short while, you'll see that witnessing is not a personal phenomenon.\NYou're witnessing whether you like it or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.22,0:07:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Try telling yourself, telling your mind, stop witnessing.\NIt goes right down to witnessing, you don't have any control of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.07,0:07:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, you will quickly discover that consciousness is impersonal.\NYou've never even decided that you have consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.03,0:07:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,When you woke up as a small baby, there it was, looking at your little toes.\NThe capacity, consciousness then is self-existent.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.92,0:07:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The unmanifest comes to manifest, it first expresses itself as consciousness awareness\Nbefore it even begins to come into form.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.71,0:07:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So that we will observe that evolution occurs on the level of consciousness and then manifests\Nwithin the physical being.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.51,0:07:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So that we will observe that evolution occurs on the level of consciousness and then manifests within the physical being.\NSo that we will observe that evolution occurs on the level of consciousness and then manifests within the physical being.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.24,0:08:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolution does not occur as a physicality creating a different physicality, creating\Na different physicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.96,0:08:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's on the level of the invisible domain.\NWithin the invisible domain of consciousness, evolution of consciousness evolves and then
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.74,0:08:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it manifests within the physical domain.\NWhat we see in the physical domain then is the physicality, the externalization, the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.06,0:08:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,expression of the unmanifest.\NYou might say the divinity within of the self with a capital L.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.64,0:08:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, within us.\NThe Empire State Building did not arise on 34th Street, it arose within the concept of
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.45,0:08:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,its designer.\NOne day he got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.45,0:08:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Tallest building in the world, or not 34th Street.\NThere it was born, in the invisible domain of the consciousness of its creator, who then
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.92,0:08:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,excited people with this concept, excited people with this vision, think what it will\Ndo for the city of New York, think of the rentals we get.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.84,0:09:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the contractors, the designers, the sculptors, the stonemasons, the steelworkers\Nall got involved and the banks got excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.44,0:09:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The lawyers got in there and the real estate appeared and it became manifest.\NBut as you see, it went from the unmanifest, from the invisible domain, directly into the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.36,0:09:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,physical.\N34th Street did not evolve into the Empire State Building.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.67,0:09:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So we want to overcome another delusion of mankind.\NI would like us all to be aware that God is at the top of this chart.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.36,0:09:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that way to God, and this way to the other place.\NWe laugh at it, but do you realize that a good part of the world, especially throughout
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.79,0:09:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,history, has had it in the opposite direction?\NIt has.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.29,0:10:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That the force of creation comes from the bottom and goes up.\NNow when we understand the material world, we realize it has no power of creation within
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.62,0:10:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,it.\NThe physical world can create anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.62,0:10:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There's not a chair in here that can create another chair.\NNot one.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.48,0:10:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NCreation comes from power to lesser power.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.97,0:10:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,As we see, the bottom is lesser power.\NThe physicality has no power of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.03,0:10:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The physical world arises out of the invisible domain.\NThat brings us up to sort of defining the nature of God then.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.68,0:10:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's clarify something about God and clarify another great misunderstanding.\N1.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.00,0:10:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The human ego\NGod has been greatly maligned throughout history, and the human ego is what's from 200 down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.29,0:11:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the ego.\NWe see the human ego has to do with revenge, retaliation, jealousy, competitiveness, sensitivity,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.09,0:11:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,paranoia, rage, revenge, destructiveness.\NThat is the level of demons, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.48,0:11:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not the level of angels.\NAngels are this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.28,0:11:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,They're this way.\NDevils are that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.28,0:11:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?\NLet's get clear about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.01,0:11:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NThroughout time, because man didn't know much about anything, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.01,0:11:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Man really didn't know much about anything.\NStill doesn't, probably, on the grand time scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.94,0:11:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But, you know, our present life is only written within 100 years, you know, and I've lived\Nthrough a good part of it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.94,0:11:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, radios were brand new when I hit this planet.\NMuch less TV or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.29,0:11:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we consider the modern world is really just the way it is today.\NYou know?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.36,0:11:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The modern world is really just the last second.\NThroughout most of mankind, human life throughout history, we said the consciousness level of
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.48,0:12:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,every century was about 190, which is below truth.\NBelow truth is easy to sell people that which is false.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.48,0:12:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is most prevalent and still exists considerably in large parts of the world,\Nincluding our own country, in certain branches of certain religions, is the confusion of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.48,0:12:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,God with the demons.\NThe human ego tends to blame God for its own creations.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.48,0:12:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,War is an invention of the human ego.\NIt is not of divine origin.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.84,0:12:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the difficulty with a person who is well into the 400s, which is the intellect,\Nthe advanced intellect, is that the negative depictions of God have made atheists of many
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.41,0:12:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,honest men.\NThey know intuitively that God couldn't be that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.57,0:12:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to believe in a God who is arbitrary, vengeful, savage, angry, fitful, paranoid,\Njealous, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.70,0:13:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensitive.\NSo what happens, Freud was correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.78,0:13:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud and God monotheism.\NFreud said that God was a projection from the human unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.47,0:13:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he made a mistake and he said, and therefore there isn't any.\NThat's why Freud calibrates at 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.60,0:13:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The leading scientists in the history, Sir Isaac Newton, Sigmund Freud, Einstein, they\Nall calibrated 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.97,0:13:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a great big block to get from 499, which is the intellect, to 500, which is the\Nheart.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.97,0:13:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very hard to make that jump.\NIn our society, it's very seldom made.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.23,0:14:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,0.4% of the population ever gets from their mind, from their head, into the heart.\NSo Freud made the mistake in thinking, if there is no false gods, therefore there are
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.48,0:14:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,no true gods.\NWhat he should have said was, the negative gods, the gods who kill you and savage you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.31,0:14:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and throw you into hell forever, are a projection from man's unconsciousness out of his guilt,\Nout of his guilt and fear he rejects onto deity, which he really knows nothing about
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.60,0:14:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,unless he's experienced the presence of God, his own imaginations.\NCarl Jung went beyond that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.49,0:14:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Carl Jung affirmed the spiritual reality of man.\NCarl Jung calibrates at 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.49,0:14:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,540.\NEinstein, Freud is at 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.88,0:14:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Carl Jung affirmed the reality of man's spirit.\NCalibrates at 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.68,0:14:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So the correct conclusion is, if the negative gods are really man's imagination, projections\Nof his own unconscious guilt and fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.00,0:15:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,then the real god must be something beyond that.\NIf a false god is all that is negative, then a real god must be something that is rather positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.15,0:15:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, probably to this audience that seems rather obvious,\Nbut if you look throughout mankind's history, you'll see that is not obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.31,0:15:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The negative gods, all kinds of sacrifices made to them, etc.\NOne time I had a catatonic patient.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.13,0:15:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I hadn't spoken in years and he was laying on the floor.\NAnd I was pretty telepathic in those days.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.42,0:15:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you some of my own experiences later to explain that.\NAnyway, there was a period of years where I was extremely telepathic.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.42,0:15:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So this catatonic is laying on the floor.\NHe hasn't spoken in 20 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.42,0:15:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to specialize in schizophrenia and they brought patients from all over the world.\NSo this guy got flown in from someplace, Hamburg or Paris or someplace, wrapped up in wet sheets.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.61,0:16:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And he laid on the floor in this catatonic stupor, mute, wouldn't speak.\NSo anyway, I just sort of looked at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.84,0:16:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought, well, God, what do you want me to do with this one?\NAnd telepathically, I got what was going on with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.84,0:16:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And telepathically, I answered him.\NI said, you're blaming God for the machinations of the ego, productions of your own ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.84,0:16:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And he jumped off the floor and he started talking and the nurse about fell over.\NAnd the reason I knew it is because I might as well tell you my own spiritual experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.00,0:16:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sort of comical.\NBut I had been through something of the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.64,0:16:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So I intuited exactly where he was at.\NBecause at a rather young age, I had a lot of unusual spiritual experiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.21,0:16:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And after a number of them, one of them was I was standing out in the woods.\NAnd suddenly out of nowhere came a vision of the totality of human suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.44,0:17:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, in its complete entirety and totality.\NIt was like some infinite part of consciousness to which I was connected.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.85,0:17:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Which was capable of comprehending some such a great immensity.\NSo this, it was non-intellectual.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.85,0:17:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the sameness of the totality of the suffering of all mankind throughout all of time.\NIt was so staggering that I instantly became an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.11,0:17:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said, any God that could allow this cannot be a God to me.\NSo goodbye, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.14,0:17:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I became a rabid atheist, a very devout atheist.\NAnd I got straight A's.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.14,0:17:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Theology.\NAnd I was always interested in the subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.43,0:17:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, this, to attribute a negativity to God is to totally misconceive of the nature of God, you see.\NThat which is unmanifest, that which is unmanifest, which radiates forth its infinite potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.97,0:18:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and calibrates in extreme high numbers, then,\Nis the level of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.97,0:18:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows nothing of human frailty, couldn't care less.\NAnd much less would feel offended and have to, you know, seek revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.97,0:18:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,To seek revenge, your consciousness would have to be 200 below.\NBecause you would first of all have to see yourself as a separate entity who is vulnerable to attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.36,0:18:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Which would mean you're not divinity.\NSo anything that seeks revenge cannot be divinity by definition.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.36,0:18:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth of that which you are is absolutely invulnerable.\NUnassailable.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.53,0:18:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.\NSo now, we did mention a few things that made these kind of subjects perhaps interesting to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.52,0:18:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I was on the radio today for a couple of hours.\NThat's not a good thing to do before you're going to give up all of your drives.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.52,0:18:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But it came out that way.\NSo from 9 to 11, I had a two-hour program.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.68,0:19:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And they asked me about some of these things and so I know what they were interested in.\NSo I'll just say them to you because you're not asking questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.68,0:19:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I could just hear them.\NBut the interesting thing about this particular lifetime...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.68,0:19:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, everybody in the audience presumes there's a Dr. Hawkins here speaking to you.\NWell, that's interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.68,0:19:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, it's consciousness itself.\NIt's actually consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.68,0:19:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?\NWhen you stop identifying yourself as a physicality or a specific ego or locality,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.84,0:19:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,then what you realize, what exists is consciousness itself.\NAnd the way it came about in my own experience was...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.84,0:19:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was about three, when I was about three years old, there was no awareness of existence.\NSuddenly at age three, there was a profound confrontation with existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.84,0:19:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that I exist.\NThere were no words for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.67,0:20:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It was not a verbal experience.\NThere was a stunning awareness of existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.67,0:20:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And instantly came its dualistic opposite, nonexistence.\NInstantly, I saw the dilemma of existence versus nonexistence.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.73,0:20:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And it became obvious that if I exist, the potentiality had been there for me not to have existed.\NAnd so out of assuming I existed, because that seemed to be what was going on,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.85,0:20:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,there came the possibility of nonexistence.\NAnd there was the conflict that so-called duality of existence versus nonexistence.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.04,0:20:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.\NTo solve that duality,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.04,0:20:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness has to be around 850 or 900 or so.\NThe duality of existence versus nonexistence doesn't even come up to about 850 or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.04,0:20:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, this was a profound confrontation,\Nand it really was the setting of the spiritual lesson project,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.77,0:21:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the spiritual project of this lifetime.\NAnd then in teenage years,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.16,0:21:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the personal individual self,\Nif I thought, who am I,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.16,0:21:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,would begin to disappear.\NAnd there was just an infinite presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.16,0:21:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And that would sort of scare me that my self is disappearing.\NSo I would cling to my personal self and give it lots of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.08,0:21:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and think the word David sitting in his seat.\NWell, I was pretty bright also at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.66,0:21:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I graduated at the end of my class in kindergarten.\NGot a straight A in crayons.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.82,0:21:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, so I had these peculiar phenomena,\Nwhich I never talked to anybody about.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.82,0:21:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I was around 12 or 13,\NI had a huge paper route in Wisconsin,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.82,0:21:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,18 miles, the biggest in the state.\NAnd it was out in the sticks.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.85,0:21:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And one time it was like 20 below zero on a blizzard,\Nand I got caught in this blizzard.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.85,0:21:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It was dark.\NI was many miles from anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.85,0:22:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I dug into a snow bank to stay out of the cold.\NIt was 20 below.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.88,0:22:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was ferocious out.\NIt really was.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.88,0:22:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And I snuck into this.\NIn Wisconsin, the snow bank's by the side of the road,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.20,0:22:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, about 15, 20 feet high.\NAnd so I dug a hole into this snow bank
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.20,0:22:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to get in out of this fierce wind.\NBecause my knees were frozen stiff,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.20,0:22:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and my pants were stiff,\Nand they even cracked instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.20,0:22:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And I climbed into this hole.\NAnd before long,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.88,0:22:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the most exquisite experience\Nof my life,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.88,0:22:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,came upon, came about.\NAny personal self disappeared,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.10,0:22:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,only an infinite, growing presence,\Nbeyond all time and all space.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.10,0:22:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And the knowingness that that which I was experiencing\Nand that which I am are one and the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.10,0:22:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond all time before all universes,\Nbefore all thoughts and worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.10,0:23:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Long after all universes come and go,\Nand that which I am exists beyond all time and space.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.10,0:23:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was obvious.\NAnd this is all wordless.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.61,0:23:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind was silent.\NAnd the exquisiteness of it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.28,0:23:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And every time it recurred,\Nthe same exquisite disinclination
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.92,0:23:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to reactivate the body,\Nre-identify with the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.92,0:23:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'd have no idea how much time.\NThis is all out of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.92,0:23:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and timeless experience.\NThe next thing was my father shaking my leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.92,0:23:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd finally come out in our 29 model 8 Ford\Nto find him,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.92,0:23:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to find his son who was lost in the blizzard.\NAnd I looked at him,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.92,0:23:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and I saw that if I did not come in the back,\Nin the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.37,0:23:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,he would presume I'd died,\Nthat the body would die.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.44,0:23:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And he would be very upset by this\Nbecause he believed that I am my body,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.44,0:23:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and he believes he's his body,\Nso he believed I'm my body.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.44,0:23:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I didn't resume it,\Nhe would go into enormous grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.44,0:24:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I love my father a great deal.\NSo for his sake,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.85,0:24:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I came back...\Nwhich I've sort of since regretted,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.36,0:24:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,but anyway...\NI came back in the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.36,0:24:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and I tried to acclimatize myself\Nto how the world sees reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.36,0:24:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And I never spoke of this to anybody,\Nand the next time it happened again,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.52,0:24:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it happened...\None time it happened with a friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.52,0:24:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I was doing a technique called rebirthing,\Nand I went out of body
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.52,0:24:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,with the same infinite glowing infinity,\Nand I had no decision to breathe anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.81,0:24:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I stopped breathing,\Nand everything stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.81,0:24:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And...\NI saw that this was going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.81,0:24:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,very upsetting to my rebirther,\Nwho was going to lose his first subject in death.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.81,0:24:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And I could see the headlines,\Nand I got...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.81,0:24:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,telepathically, he's saying,\Nbreathe, hey, breathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.81,0:24:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You should love me, breathe.\NIn that instant,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.81,0:24:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I just really loved him intensely,\Nand frankly, I did breathe for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.81,0:24:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I really did.\NI hang him up with a dead body here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.81,0:25:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And see, because the world consumes that\Nwhen this stops breathing in and out and all,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.81,0:25:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're dead.\NYou know, this is very naive,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.81,0:25:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's the way the world sees things.\NSo, you have to go along with the world
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.81,0:25:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and sort of humor it in a way.\NAnd in 1965,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.97,0:25:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it was a state of incredible despair.\NDon't forget I was an atheist at this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.97,0:25:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and a very devout one.\NI was a devout atheist, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.16,0:25:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I was against these negative gods,\Nand wasn't really an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.38,0:25:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just against all these concepts of God\Nas a monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.51,0:25:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't have any positive concept of God,\Nbut I knew that whatever people believed in
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.51,0:25:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't hang in with my experience.\NSo, anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.51,0:25:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I was at the depths of spiritual despair\Nand physically ill
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.51,0:25:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and in a catastrophic state.\NAnd I went into a state of black despair
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.18,0:26:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond all description.\NThere's really levels of hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.18,0:26:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Levels of hell.\NThere are a lot of levels of hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.50,0:26:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And the higher levels\Nwhere you're being tortured and fried and all that,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.50,0:26:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that's just the beginning.\NThat's kindergarten.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.50,0:26:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And you go to an existential despair\Nin which the blackness is beyond all description.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.50,0:26:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I said,\Nif there is a God,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.50,0:26:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't hold my breath,\Nif there is a God,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.50,0:26:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,all right, I'd ask his help.\NI thought, well,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.50,0:26:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, before you die,\Nyou go on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.50,0:26:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably best to play it safe.\NGet on the other side,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.50,0:26:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and he says,\Nyou know,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.50,0:26:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you were saying.\NAnyway, it was,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.20,0:26:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what I did.\NAs a profound atheist,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.43,0:26:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I really did not hold my breath.\NI didn't think I was going to answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.43,0:26:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But, you know,\Nhollering down an empty alleyway there,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.43,0:26:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's nobody there to hear,\Nbut you did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.43,0:27:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's on the record that you did it.\NSo I hollered down the empty alley,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.43,0:27:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and then everything disappeared.\NEverything disappeared,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.00,0:27:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and I have no idea how much time went by.\NBut on January 10, 1965 then,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.04,0:27:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly that which had been David,\Nthat which the world calls David,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.04,0:27:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,disappeared completely.\NThere was no individual self.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.04,0:27:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Thought stopped.\NNo mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.04,0:27:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Only an infinite presence,\Nwhich is and still is all that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.51,0:27:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It expresses itself\Nas the creation observed and witnessed
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.51,0:27:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,by the senses,\Nbut the divinity of its nature
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.51,0:27:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is shown forth with a radiance\Nthat is so stunning as to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.51,0:27:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,leave no question.\NAnd then the body went about its own business,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.99,0:27:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,which it still does.\NAs you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.99,0:27:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,it moves and it's like a puppet.\NIt goes,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.99,0:27:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,it runs itself.\NIt has nothing to do with the person itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.99,0:28:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,People think,\Nwell, I decided to move my arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.12,0:28:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an illusion.\NNo, the arm moved itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.12,0:28:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and then instantly the ego jumps in\Nand says,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.12,0:28:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I moved it.\NNo, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.12,0:28:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It moved itself before the eye says that.\NIn meditation you can discover that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.12,0:28:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So this body was there\Nlike another piece of furniture in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.18,0:28:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I really had no interest in it.\NAnd the mind had disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.18,0:28:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no thinkingness,\Nand everything happened of its own
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.18,0:28:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in this infinite presence.\NAnd that condition lasted.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.88,0:28:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't possible to think in words.\NNo words came forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.88,0:28:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,All that is is known forever,\Nand to understand one grain of sand
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.95,0:28:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,is to understand the universe.\NSo there's nothing you need to know
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.95,0:28:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,because once you are all that is,\Nthere's nothing you need.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.95,0:28:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So the sense of completeness was present.\NTo this day there's nothing I need.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.16,0:29:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,People say,\Nwhat do you want for Christmas?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.16,0:29:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing I want for Christmas.\NDo you want to win the lottery?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.20,0:29:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I don't want to win the lottery.\NThere's absolutely nothing I need or want.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.20,0:29:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Because once you are all that is,\Nthere's nothing lacking.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.20,0:29:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And if there's nothing lacking,\Nthere's obviously nothing you would gain
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.20,0:29:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,by getting anything.\NSo there was the loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.29,0:29:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The first thing that happened\Nwas the loss of all the drives
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.29,0:29:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that are considered human.\NThe desire for success,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.29,0:29:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,for money,\Nfor security.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.39,0:29:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,All the things that people consider\Nimportant in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.39,0:29:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly became meaningless.\NAnd so by ordinary human standards
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.39,0:29:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I was motivationless.\NNo motivation for anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.06,0:29:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And the body went about its way,\Nwhich it still does.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.06,0:29:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a karmic wind-up toy.\NIt's like a puppet.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.06,0:29:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like my little friend.\NA lot of times I wish it had fur.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.06,0:29:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say,\Nyou know if this thing had fur
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.06,0:29:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd really like it a lot more.\NIt'd be more fun,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.06,0:29:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,like a kitty.\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.06,0:29:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So this thing is my happy puppet\Nand it goes about its business.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.06,0:30:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been doing that since 1965 by itself.\NI don't have to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.25,0:30:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It just does whatever it's going to do.\NSo that condition,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.05,0:30:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that condition then was difficult\Nto function in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.05,0:30:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And actually I did leave the world.\NI had a huge practice in New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.05,0:30:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And I moved to a small town\Nwhere I lived by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.05,0:30:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's a monastery for one person.\NJust a monastery for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.21,0:30:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And I lost identification\Nwith the physical body.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.21,0:30:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can remember one time\NI hadn't eaten for some days either.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.21,0:30:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a hard thing\Nfor me to do too.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.21,0:30:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And I walked past the mirror\Nand there was somebody in the house with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.21,0:30:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It gave me a mental shock.\NI saw this person walking through the mirror
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.37,0:30:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and realized it was me.\NOh God.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.37,0:30:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It was shocking for a second.\NAnyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.37,0:30:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,so the loss of identification with physicality.\NSo what we're saying is that
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.50,0:31:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in certain peculiar persons then\Nthis spontaneous occurrence
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.53,0:31:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that also occurs as a result of meditation,\NI had done Zen meditation
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.53,0:31:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and some things before that experience.\NBut all of a sudden
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.98,0:31:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,one can transcend the identification\Nwith the linear world,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.98,0:31:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the Newtonian paradigm of reality\Nand shift to the non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.98,0:31:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all we're saying.\NAnd what the world considers spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.98,0:31:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is really just the non-linear.\NAnd what it considers material
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.98,0:31:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is the linear.\NNow the two coincide.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.40,0:31:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time\Nthat there is a linear reality here,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.40,0:31:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the chairs and the desks and all,\Nthis is all here within space.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.40,0:31:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can identify either with the chairs\Nand the physicality
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.40,0:31:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,or as what happened to me,\NI am the space
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.46,0:31:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in which all of this occurs\Nthroughout all of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.46,0:31:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the panorama,\Nthe witness,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.46,0:32:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the movie of what's going on\Ncomes and goes
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.46,0:32:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and it actually has no effect on me whatsoever.\NUsually it's amusing
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.46,0:32:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,if anything.\NSo for some years
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.46,0:32:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I had trouble communicating with the world\Nbecause the mind is silent,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.46,0:32:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,which it is to this day.\NThat which I am is silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.46,0:32:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It says nothing.\NAnd there was having to learn how to speak
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.32,0:32:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,which people would say things\Nand it didn't make any...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.32,0:32:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean they would talk\Nand it made no sense at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.32,0:32:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It was totally irrelevant\Nand not even believable.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.32,0:32:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I found that within myself\NI would ask the spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.32,0:32:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,what does that mean?\NAnd then I would get what that meant.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.32,0:32:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was like a translate.\NA translator within myself
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.32,0:32:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that would transform\Nwhat is being said
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.32,0:32:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world of form\Nso it was comprehensible
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.32,0:32:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world of non-form.\NThat's the only way I can explain it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.32,0:32:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo this then has to do
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.12,0:32:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,with the two different dimensions\Nin which life can be experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.12,0:32:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,from the linear\Nand from the non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.12,0:33:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,How to move from the linear domain\Ninto the non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.12,0:33:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We talk about that as spiritual work.\NSpiritual work, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.12,0:33:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual work is merely a willingness.\NPeople say,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.12,0:33:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,how can I evolve\Nin my level of consciousness?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.12,0:33:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very simple, you know.\NChoice is here at all times.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.12,0:33:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And what we do is\Nwe choose to be forgiving.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.12,0:33:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We choose to be helpful to others.\NThese are all options
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.16,0:33:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that are available to us at all times.\NThe willingness to be kind and considerate
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.89,0:33:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to all that exists\Nfrom moment to moment
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.89,0:33:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,within and without.\NSo to be kind and forgiving
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.89,0:33:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,means towards yourself\Nas well as to everything that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.89,0:33:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that exists.\NSomebody asked me,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.42,0:33:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,how do you define God?\NI said, well, in my experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.42,0:34:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,God is the capacity\Nto manifest existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.70,0:34:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing has the capacity\Nwithin itself to exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.28,0:34:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have enough power.\NIt doesn't have within itself
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.92,0:34:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the power of creation.\NThat which is unmanifest then,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.92,0:34:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is the source of existence itself.\NYou ask, where is God?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.04,0:34:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the capacity to exist,\Nthe fact that you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.94,0:34:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,is the most direct manifestation\Nof the presence of God
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.94,0:34:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,within yourself.\NSo the current book I'm writing on
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.22,0:34:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,is called\NThe Eye of the Eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.22,0:34:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,spelled E-Y-E of the eye.\NThe Eye of the Eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.22,0:34:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,When you say eye,\Nwhat is it you're saying
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.41,0:34:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,when you say eye?\NWho do you mean by eye?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.41,0:34:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mean your physical body?\NIs that the eye?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.41,0:34:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the eye owns your physical body.\NIt has one.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.41,0:35:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mean your mind?\NWhat is it that allows us to say eye?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.79,0:35:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The person assumes\Nthat there is an individual,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.79,0:35:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,specific thing called eye,\Na me, me, it's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.04,0:35:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This eye, this self,\Nand that it's temporal,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.36,0:35:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it's temporary,\Nand everybody therefore fears death
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.36,0:35:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,because they say,\Nwell, when you croak,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.46,0:35:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,say goodbye to eye.\NActually, it's the other way around.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.84,0:35:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's, there is an infinite eye.\NWhen we say consciousness itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.09,0:35:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness itself is a quality,\Nimpersonal quality,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.09,0:35:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,within your own consciousness,\Nwhich accounts for your awareness,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.09,0:35:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,your capacity to know,\Nto know that you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.35,0:35:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's coming out of an impersonal quality\Ncalled consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.35,0:35:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This consciousness manifests itself\Nin the belief, mistakenly,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.35,0:36:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that you are a very limited thing\Nthat just got here
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.35,0:36:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and is going to be leaving\Nbefore a few years,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.35,0:36:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and you had a beginning\Nand now you will end
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.35,0:36:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,in this physicality.\NThat which really says eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.66,0:36:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,if you do it just,\Nit doesn't take very long in meditation
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.66,0:36:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to go to the source\Nof what is it that is saying eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.66,0:36:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What enables you to even say\Nthat you exist?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.66,0:36:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That the capacity to say personal eye\Nis coming from the endowment
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.12,0:36:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of an impersonal eye.\NThe impersonal eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.12,0:36:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the same in all of us,\Nthe self and me with a capital S,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.12,0:36:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is the same as the self\Nin everyone here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.12,0:36:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone here exists.\NWe have agreement on that, don't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.86,0:36:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We do agree we all exist.\NWe do agree that there is a capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.40,0:37:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to know that one exists.\NIt is not provable.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.44,0:37:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot really prove that you exist.\NYou can put forth all kinds of data
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.44,0:37:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and that will impress people\Nin the low of the 400s
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.44,0:37:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,as convincing logic,\Nbut knowingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.44,0:37:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to exist is a knowingness\Nwhich is beyond logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.56,0:37:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so science will take us up.\NBut we notice that the level of the intellect
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.30,0:37:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is in the 400s.\NThe 400s, things always act mysteriously too.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.55,0:37:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I think they are wonderful.\NAnyway, you see here the,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.48,0:37:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a little thing,\Na little light thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.48,0:37:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It probably doesn't work either.\NOh, no, it does work.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.40,0:37:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how it works,\Nbut you push a button and it lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.72,0:37:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's wonderful.\NI don't know, the world of thingness
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.17,0:37:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,has not been my,\NI don't have a computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.26,0:37:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm as lazy as I think\Nhow it operates or what it says.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.26,0:38:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, you see that the level of science\Nis the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.41,0:38:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, science then is capable\Nof understanding logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.41,0:38:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And the only thing with man's knowledge\Nis people don't put the limits on,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.41,0:38:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the limits on their knowledge.\NScience cannot say anything about
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.41,0:38:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the nonlinear domain.\NIt has no validity.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.05,0:38:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care what science says\Nabout spirituality
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.05,0:38:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because it has no capacity\Nto comprehend it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.05,0:38:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't have the slightest idea\Nwhere to start.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.05,0:38:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Likewise, it's best\Nthat spirituality stays out of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.79,0:38:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,When the church makes pronouncements\Nabout Galileo and the sun
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.46,0:38:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,going around the earth,\Nthe earth going around the sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.46,0:38:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,it's out of its bailiwick.\NAnd you like having an opinion
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.46,0:38:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,on outside matters.\NOne thing that's beautiful
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.52,0:38:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,about the 12-step programs\Nis the purity of the spiritual essence of it
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.52,0:38:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is that they have no opinion\Non outside matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.52,0:39:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That's really a wonderful thing.\NAnd as you're driving along,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.72,0:39:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,just think how relieving it is\Nnot to have any opinion about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.72,0:39:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Gosh, I don't have to have an opinion\Nabout anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.72,0:39:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, what a relief, you know what I mean?\NYou don't really need an opinion
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.72,0:39:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,about anything, no.\NIn fact, it's great not to have
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.72,0:39:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,any opinions about anything.\NOne way to tell whether you're making
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.58,0:39:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,good spiritual progress,\Nand here's a very good test,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.58,0:39:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is if you enjoy letting somebody\Nget ahead of you in traffic.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.58,0:39:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If you get like a feel-good glow,\Ncome on in, fella.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.84,0:39:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Give them a break.\NGee, the person goes,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.87,0:39:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,whoa.\NAnd you can see them fall over, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.87,0:39:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a little bit of love\Nknocks people out, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.87,0:39:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You come up to the stoplight,\Nlook at the person in the next car
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.03,0:39:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and smile at them.\NMy God, it causes terror and panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.03,0:39:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Call 911.\NThere's a man smiling here in the next car.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.92,0:40:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure they're not the opposite sex.\NThat's the safe side.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.92,0:40:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand,\Nmaybe even the same sex nowadays,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.92,0:40:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NIt's best not to smile at strangers.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.92,0:40:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so you see\Nthe evolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.05,0:40:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,become sort of automatic\Nonce you're familiar with certain things.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.05,0:40:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Just the things we've talked about today.\NYour consciousness is not the same as it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.05,0:40:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize that it's on a trajectory.\NLet's see how this consciousness works.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.05,0:40:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,These energy fields in chaos theory\Nand chaos theory,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.05,0:40:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,nonlinear dynamics theory,\Nare organized around an attractor field.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.21,0:40:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,These levels of consciousness\Ndominate the human mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.21,0:40:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The human mind, like, picks up\Nand is entrained
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.21,0:40:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,by these powerful energy fields.\NThe field holds dominion
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.47,0:40:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,over man's consciousness.\NThe minute you ascribe to a certain attitude,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.63,0:41:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you now become subject to being dominated\Nby the entire set of attitudes
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.63,0:41:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that go with that field.\NThe minute you give a lot of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.97,0:41:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to right and wrong,\Nyou are now stuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.97,0:41:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Right and wrong is one of the great dualities.\NBut to become involved spiritually,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.97,0:41:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to transcend\Nand see right and wrong are very irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.97,0:41:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It really makes no difference\Nwhether the thing is right or wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.97,0:41:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you jump that duality,\Nyou're not stuck there,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.97,0:41:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and instantly your consciousness\Nwill rise up into the high five hundreds.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.97,0:41:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The high five hundreds\Nis not interested in right and wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.97,0:41:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The people who hand out turkeys at the mission,\Nthey don't try to decide
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.97,0:41:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,who's justified in having a turkey.\NOr not having a turkey.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.97,0:41:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the divinity of God,\Nthe love of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.13,0:41:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,radiates equally on all.\NIt doesn't get involved in judgmentalism.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.13,0:41:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are levels of consciousness,\Nand we'll just sort of go over them
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.89,0:41:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you get what they're about.\NVery at the lowest we have
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.08,0:41:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling miserable.\NThe world is a miserable place.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.08,0:42:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is our view of life.\NIf your consciousness is down here,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.08,0:42:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,this is how you experience life.\NThis is what life looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.08,0:42:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Miserable.\NShame is the predominant.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.08,0:42:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And its energy is 20.\NI'll teach you the pictures you see
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.49,0:42:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,on the front of Time magazine\Nof starving Ethiopian infants
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.52,0:42:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,who are born with AIDS\Nand have starved to death
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.52,0:42:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,probably by the age of six months.\NThe mother doesn't even know
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.52,0:42:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,what to do with the body.\NShe just leaves it by the side of the road
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.52,0:42:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,where the flies gather on it.\NThat's all these people here.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.42,0:42:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Whole subcontinents come in\Nat these levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.42,0:42:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Not enough energy to pull\Nenough energy from life to even exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.42,0:42:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Interestingly enough,\Nwe can calibrate the level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.69,0:42:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of an infant the minute it's born.\NYou're born into this world
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.36,0:43:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,at a certain level of consciousness.\NWhere did that arise from?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.40,0:43:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness, then, is an ongoing thing.\NIn my own observation,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.44,0:43:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,this is my own observation\Nand my own conclusions
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.44,0:43:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and my own research,\Nthat consciousness evolves
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.05,0:43:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,from down here\Non up to divinity itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.05,0:43:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And it may take many physicalities\Nto do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.12,0:43:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I view consciousness\Nas a continuum
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.12,0:43:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that seeks periodically\Nto physicalize.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.69,0:43:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,When we talk about karma,\Nwhat we're saying is that
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.54,0:43:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,every action manifests\Na vibration or a frequency
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.24,0:43:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,which registers somewhere.\NAnd this somewhere carries on.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.24,0:43:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And it has consequences eventually.\NEvery religion says,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.28,0:43:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,as you sow, you shall reap.\NIt doesn't say
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.28,0:43:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that you'll necessarily physically manifest again.\NBut it does say
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.28,0:44:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're going to go\Nfrom one level to another
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.28,0:44:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and where you go to\Ndepends on
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.28,0:44:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,what kind of vibrations you've set up\Nin your spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.72,0:44:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,your soul,\Nor whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.33,0:44:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,My own view of it is that\Nthese levels here
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.91,0:44:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,really are of the spirit.\NAnd these,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.68,0:44:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you're like a cork.\NYou're like a cork in the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.68,0:44:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In the sea of consciousness,\Nyour calibrated level determines
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.68,0:44:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,where you rise or fall as a cork.\NAnd when you leave the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.12,0:44:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,this is just,\Nyou don't have to buy anything I'm saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.12,0:44:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,when you leave the body,\Nthe spirit leaves the body
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.12,0:44:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and I've been out of body\Nand I know the spirit does leave the body
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.12,0:44:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,because I've been down there and up there\Nand we'll look after the body down in a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.12,0:44:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And where the spirit goes\Nwould then depend on its vibration,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.12,0:44:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,its buoyancy.\NSo these frequencies then would determine
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.25,0:44:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,if there is such a thing as a spirit\Nthat supersedes the physicality,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.25,0:45:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,where it goes.\NWhere it goes is it would just float
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.25,0:45:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to its own level.\NThis to me is the absolute justice of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.25,0:45:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,God is incapable of injustice\Nbecause each one of us by our own actions
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.25,0:45:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,sets our own karmic vibrational pattern\Nand thereby determines our destiny
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.44,0:45:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in the great beyond,\Nwhich is actually here,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.44,0:45:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but it sounds like the great beyond.\NSo these people came in here
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.05,0:45:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,at a pretty low level.\NAnd here we see people who see God as condemning.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.72,0:45:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Here God despises us.\NHere God is vindictive.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.72,0:45:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He's always getting even with you.\NHere God is that which condemns you
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.76,0:45:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and disdains you and is punitive,\Ndenies what you need to survive life,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.76,0:45:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is vengeful.\NSo you see the view of God
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.32,0:45:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,depends on your life.\NIt depends on your level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.32,0:45:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The life view is life is miserable.\NThis is an evil world,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.32,0:45:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,a hopeless world,\Na tragic world,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.32,0:46:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,a frightening world,\Na disappointing world.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.32,0:46:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a world of anger,\Na demanding,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.36,0:46:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,or is it a feasible,\Nsatisfactory,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.36,0:46:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,hopeful world of opportunity?\NIt's all how you look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.36,0:46:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,God is either a punitive,\Nhorrible thing that you live in dread of,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.36,0:46:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,or he's the source of freedom,\Ninspiration,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.36,0:46:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,mercy,\Nwisdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.36,0:46:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,love,\Nand it's actually your own self with a capital S.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.36,0:46:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we go through these emotional levels.\NWe go through these calibrated energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.54,0:46:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and we see the emotion that is associated with them.\NDown here we have blame.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.54,0:46:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,People spend their whole lifetimes blaming everything.\NWe have whole continents.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.60,0:46:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The Middle East spent the last couple thousand years.\NFirst they blame one,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.60,0:46:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,then they blame the other.\NThey shoot over a bomb,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.60,0:46:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,then they retaliate with another bomb.\NThis amuses them by the millennium.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.60,0:46:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They go on for thousands of years doing that.\NThey live off the spleen.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.76,0:46:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They live off the energy of hate.\NHate and blame.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.76,0:46:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,When you get a little bit better,\Nyou go into depression.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.76,0:47:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Come out of hate and vindictive killingness,\Nand you lay on the floor and sob.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.76,0:47:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You at least come up to regret,\Nwhich is,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.02,0:47:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the beginning of decency,\Nyou know,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.02,0:47:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,at least you regret that you bombed all those people.\NNow you get a little bit anxious about,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.02,0:47:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,am I doing the right thing or not?\NNow that you can get your energy up to cravingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.02,0:47:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the level of the addictions.\NHere's the addictions.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.02,0:47:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You're stuck in the solar plexus.\NI'm in this wantingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.02,0:47:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It cannot be satisfied.\NCravingness is an energy fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.02,0:47:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you cannot satisfy it.\NThe minute you get through this,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.44,0:47:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you're planning on the next.\NThere's no way out of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.11,0:47:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we get up to the levels of hatred,\Nlevels of pride and scorn.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.11,0:47:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And these are what's happening in the process in consciousness.\NHere, what happens is you eliminate yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.11,0:47:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Elimination is what happens here.\NHere we have destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.11,0:47:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Before you get eliminated,\Nyou get destroyed,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.11,0:48:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,pounded into powder\Nbefore they dump you in the dumpster.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.11,0:48:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we have despondency,\Nwithdrawal,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.11,0:48:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,enslavement.\NHere's the level of addictions,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.11,0:48:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,which many of us work with.\NThe level of enslavement.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.11,0:48:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You're hooked in the solar plexus of wantingness.\NThere is no satisfaction for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.11,0:48:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So it goes on and on continually running you.\NYou're enslaved by cravingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.75,0:48:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Hatred leads to aggression.\NYou've got Adolf Hitler
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.75,0:48:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and militaristic hateful people\Nwith inflated egos
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.75,0:48:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,who are scornful of others\Nand live out of pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.94,0:48:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Deutschland über alles.\NAny sane person, when you think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.58,0:48:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you mean, Deutschland über alles?\N70 million people bought it
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.58,0:48:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and so they all died.\NAnyway, so here you have this inflated ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.68,0:48:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, once you get above it,\Nyou have the level of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.84,0:48:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the emotion here is one of affirmation.\NYou take the first step in the 12-step group.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.84,0:49:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I admit the truth about myself.\NWow, the minute you admit truth about yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.84,0:49:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not a genius.\NOh, gee, that's a hard one.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.67,0:49:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was at the head of my class in kindergarten.\NBut you're not a genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.67,0:49:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so affirmation.\NThis leads to trust, optimism.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.67,0:49:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And here is a very important level for all of us\Nbecause many of us work in the health field.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.67,0:49:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgiveness.\NHow do you see a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.67,0:49:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,In comes the kid to your institution\Nwho's done really awful things
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.67,0:49:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and is awesomely negative,\Ntelling you where to go with their finger
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.67,0:49:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the minute they say hello to you.\NSo forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.37,0:49:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The capacity to be compassionate.\NThese are the levels of transcendence
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.37,0:49:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and understanding.\NAnd we move on up through reverence.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.37,0:49:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The reverence for all of life.\NThe reverence for all that lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.37,0:49:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NThe reverence that the source of existence
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.37,0:49:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of all that is\Nis divinity itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.14,0:50:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The moment of revelation was so stunning\Nit's just profound.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.14,0:50:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just like you walked out of a dark cave\Nthat you lived into all your life
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.68,0:50:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,into a field of snow\Nin midday.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.68,0:50:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just beyond all comprehension.\NTotally wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.71,0:50:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,All these belief systems\Nthinking this.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.74,0:50:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You come into what's called\Nthe ineffable.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.74,0:50:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's called enlightenment\Nin which you realize that
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.74,0:50:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is divine\Nand that which is the source and the essence
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.74,0:50:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,of your own self\Nare one and the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.45,0:50:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The various religions may have confused it\Nby using different terminology.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.64,0:50:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But in essence all of them say\Nthat the ultimate reality
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.64,0:50:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is within you.\NJesus said where he said it was
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.64,0:50:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,heaven is within you.\NIt's not elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.64,0:51:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not some other time.\NYou are spiritually committed.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.22,0:51:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the most intense way\Nto reach a state of enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.22,0:51:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,or greater awareness?\NThe realization that
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.64,0:51:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,reality can be only discovered\Nin the absolute instant of now.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.64,0:51:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It is in this absolute\Nsplit nanomicrosecond
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.31,0:51:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,of now\Nthat the reality shines forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.31,0:51:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like\Nthe mind is so
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.60,0:51:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,beclouded with clouds\Nthat you don't see
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.60,0:51:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the sun in the sky\Nexcept for a split second
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.60,0:51:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,between two clouds.\NThat's what the Buddha said
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.66,0:51:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and I discovered that what he said was true.\NHe says that the great infinite void
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.66,0:51:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the infinite beingness of the universe\Nthe godness, the godhead
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.66,0:51:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the transcendent divinity\Nof the supreme of all
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.69,0:51:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is found between two thoughts.\NAnd therefore there are many
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.17,0:51:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,meditative techniques\Nin which one witnesses the thoughts going by
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.17,0:52:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,stops identifying with them\Nand there are certainly
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.30,0:52:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,some very exquisite techniques\Nto do this very thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.30,0:52:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But it is true, it is within\Nthe infinite presence of now.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.30,0:52:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And how does one transcend\Nthe infinite now?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.75,0:52:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You witness out of the mind\Nhow everything is arising
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.94,0:52:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and falling within mind\Nlike a musical note.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.32,0:52:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,When you listen to a note of music\Nit arises and
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.39,0:52:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,within the creation and experience\Nof that note is already
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.42,0:52:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it is already disappearing\Nand a new note is already
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.84,0:52:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,so you don't get caught in the melody\Nyou stay on the moment of
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.84,0:52:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the sound that is arising now\Nyou don't try to cling to it
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.84,0:52:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't try to anticipate the next moment of now\Nand you discover that what the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.84,0:52:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is trying to do all the time\Nis anticipate the next split second of now
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.84,0:52:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and control it.\NIf you watch in meditation
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.06,0:53:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,what your mind is doing\Nis trying to grab the next moment of now
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.06,0:53:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,verbalize it\Ngive it a name, give it an image, give it a form
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.98,0:53:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it is like there is an energy\Nof thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.11,0:53:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,which comes out of a primordial matrix\Nwhich is beyond form
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.65,0:53:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it is formless\Nbut it is out of this powerful goo
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.65,0:53:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that wants to constantly come into\Nbeing as a thought
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.65,0:53:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to catch it, the willingness\Nto let go of thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.65,0:53:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you will see that thinkingness\Nis an independent function all its own
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.65,0:53:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no I thinking\Nas you become enlightened you see there is no individual I
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.65,0:53:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no doer behind the doings\Nthere is no doer doing
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.26,0:53:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,what is being done now\Nit is happening of its own
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.26,0:53:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is the expression\Neverything comes into being
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.26,0:53:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,as the perfect expression\Nof its own essence
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.26,0:53:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and it does so in this instant\Neach instant it is
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.48,0:53:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it expresses the essence\Nof its own beingness
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.48,0:54:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,its own reality\Nand that is its divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.48,0:54:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,so divinity expresses itself\Nas existence
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.87,0:54:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,as beingness\Nis that what you are at this moment
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.87,0:54:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and the way to catch it at that\Nis to ride the crest
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.09,0:54:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of this exact instant\Nit would be a nano instant
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.92,0:54:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I like nano, that is a new one\NI always liked micro
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.63,0:54:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,but there is another one used in astronomy\Nmeaning even lower than micro
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.63,0:54:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget what it is now\Nbut nano seems like the greatest
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.98,0:54:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of the littlest of the littlest\Nand I just love the thought
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.98,0:54:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is nano manufacturing\Ngoing on
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.98,0:54:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,little molecules can be taught\Nhow to make themselves into a little factory
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.98,0:54:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and create I guess a whole Ford automobile\Nwho knows
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.98,0:54:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway\Nthere is a meditative technique
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.08,0:54:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,which you can do throughout the day\Nno matter what you are doing
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.56,0:55:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,one is always\Nas you look about you
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.62,0:55:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,there is your macular vision\Nand your peripheral vision
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.62,0:55:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,macular vision is the center\Nwhen you have intention about something
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.00,0:55:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the macula of the eye\Nis focusing on a specific point
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.10,0:55:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,because you are going to do something with it\Nyou are going to eat it, kill it
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.10,0:55:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,mate with it, buy it\Nstore it, paint it
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.95,0:55:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the peripheral vision is only aware\Nof your general positionality
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.95,0:55:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in life\Nand the more spiritually evolved
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.27,0:55:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you get, the more you tend to live\Nin peripheral vision
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.27,0:55:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,what is going on in macular vision\Nbecomes less and less important
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.27,0:55:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,it is just the work of the ego\Nand the more detached you become
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.46,0:55:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the details of what is going on\Nbecomes less and less important
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.46,0:55:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,what is important is the essence\Nyou do that yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.49,0:55:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,when you walk into a room\Nyou are aware of two things
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.49,0:56:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,you are aware of what you are looking at\Nbut you are also quickly getting the whole deal
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.49,0:56:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I mean\Nthe size of the amphitheater
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.49,0:56:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the likelihood of finding a seat\Nthe type of a crowd
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.49,0:56:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy field\Nall the boards go by
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.49,0:56:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and bushes go by\Nand you don't get caught in any of them
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.49,0:56:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and you are aware that something\Nthat is not any of that out there
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.49,0:56:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,is witnessing all that out there\Nand that type of meditation brings you to
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.49,0:56:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the awareness that there is something witnessing\Nthat witnessing
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.49,0:56:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,is happening of its own\Nit is totally impersonal
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.49,0:56:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no personal eye that is witnessing\Nany more than there is a personal eye
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.49,0:56:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,making your body do what it is doing\NI remember when I caught the body
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.49,0:56:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,in a trick\NI caught the ego one time
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.49,0:56:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I was driving somewhere\Nand a rabbit ran across the road
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.49,0:56:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,wham, the brakes went on\Nsaved the rabbit's life
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.49,0:56:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and instantly I caught that the ego\Ntook claim for that
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.49,0:57:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,said I break the brake\Nno, this time I caught it
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.49,0:57:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it had breaked itself before\NI decided to break and save the poor little bunny's life
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.88,0:57:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,oh no, it was happening of its own\Nthat which you are then
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.35,0:57:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is an absolute reality\Nthat which you are
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.35,0:57:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,exists beyond all time\Nspace and dimension
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.35,0:57:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth and reality of the self\Nof everyone here
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.54,0:57:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,we are all one and the same\Nthe self that is speaking to you
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.54,0:57:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,is your own self\Njust coming back to you
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.54,0:57:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,there is only one consciousness here\Nit activates what the saying-ness
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.54,0:57:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the wording-ness is going here\Nthat is what this body is here for
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.54,0:57:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,what is this body bumping around here for\NI could have done without years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.54,0:57:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, how would you talk\Nif you were just in visible space
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.54,0:57:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,in the middle of invisible space\Nyou couldn't talk to people
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.54,0:57:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you did, they'd get spooked\Nyou have to look like an actual person
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.54,0:58:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and talk in verbalized language\Nso that people know what you're talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.40,0:58:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,which takes us to the end of the discussion for today\Nand I thought then we'll have time for any questions
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.40,0:58:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll take a little break\Nif anybody has any questions
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.40,0:58:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we've tried to cover now\Neverything I think within the syllabus
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.40,0:58:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the first time I've ever spoken from a syllabus\Nnow it's more difficult in foreign languages
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.40,0:58:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,where you say something\Nand now you're getting enthused about it
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.40,0:58:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you have to stop because the translator\Nhas to translate it into Korean or something
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.40,0:58:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and by the time she's translated\Nyou've gotten what was it I was going to say
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.56,0:58:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that's more difficult\Nalright
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.10,0:58:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,so what I've tried to share today\Nis an overall view of consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.10,0:58:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,creation versus causality\Ncausality
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.42,0:58:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,illusions that the world holds\Nthat blinds itself
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.42,0:58:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,blinds it to what is actually the truth\Nthe difficulty in spiritual work
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.96,0:58:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,because of positionality\Nthere's only one enemy
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.96,0:59:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to all advance of consciousness\Nand that's
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.96,0:59:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,adopting a positionality\Nthat positionality then
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.96,0:59:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,twists your view of perception\Nyou cannot see the wholeness and oneness of all things
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.96,0:59:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and it divides them into\Nthinness and
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.96,0:59:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,dualistic error\Nso we tried to define
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.64,0:59:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness\Nduality versus non-duality
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.64,0:59:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,non-duality is the new dimension\NI'm speaking again at
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.64,0:59:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in Albuquerque in April\Nscience and consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.64,0:59:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,conscious\Nscience is knocking at the door
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.64,0:59:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of the linear to the non-linear\Nbecause advances in human consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.64,0:59:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,are in the non-linear domain\Nso I want to thank you for being here
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.64,0:59:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'll stay for\Nany questions you might have
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.83,0:59:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,you get to get a syllabus\Nand a certificate of attendance
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.83,1:00:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,on your way out the door\Ncalibration
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.06,1:00:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy of this audience was 411\Nwhen we started the lecture
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.06,1:00:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it went to 421 by the end of the lecture\Nthe consciousness level of a human being
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.06,1:00:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,advances about 5 points in a lifetime\Nand we jumped 10 points today
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.06,1:00:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,we jumped 10 points\Nso the
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.06,1:00:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the advance in spiritual awareness\Nwas really what you would get out of
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.06,1:00:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,two whole lifetimes\Nand the information alone does that
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.06,1:00:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,so we went from 411 to 421\Nthat's very big
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.06,1:00:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you see because we're talking about a logarithm\Nwe didn't go up 10 points
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.06,1:00:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,we went up the log\N10 points
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.54,1:00:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,those of you who understand logarithms can explain it\NI forgot what logarithms mean
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.54,1:00:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but anyway it's a big jump\Nalright now what I tried to teach people
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.54,1:00:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,is the technique of kinesiology\Nand some of these people
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.54,1:01:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,ask specific questions\Nand the way to find the answer
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.67,1:01:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is to do what I told you today\Nyou just go
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.67,1:01:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is it over 200\Nover 300 over 400
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.67,1:01:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,like that\Nnow a lot of people like to know their own level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.76,1:01:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and I find this very useful\Nyes it's very useful
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.99,1:01:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to know your own level of consciousness\Nyou can just
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.88,1:01:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,through kinesiology\Nthe best thing to do is to find somebody who's close
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.88,1:01:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,so they're available so you can do it once in a while\Nand just practice a little bit
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.88,1:01:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it's really not difficult\Nit's pretty simple
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.88,1:01:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the reason you want to know your own level of consciousness\Nis it tells you
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.09,1:01:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,what lessons you're up against\Nsee
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.09,1:01:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to know what you're at\Ntells you
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.69,1:01:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,what direction to head\Na lot of people in spiritual groups
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.69,1:01:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,are in the 400s\Nthey have gotten to the intellect
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.69,1:02:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,they're able to read and comprehend\Nthey're intellectual
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.69,1:02:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,they've read about this now they're curious\Nthey've realized that there is something beyond
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.69,1:02:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the intellect\Nso lots of people in consciousness groups
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.82,1:02:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,all over the world\Ncalibrate in the 400s
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.82,1:02:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the level of increasing awareness\Nand
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.82,1:02:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,a very good jumping off place\Nit's
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.10,1:02:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the trick there is to\Nis to stop
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.26,1:02:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,verbalizing and naming everything\Nand begin to
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.26,1:02:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,experience its essence\Nrather than its definition
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.26,1:02:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the confusion of definition\Nthe essence
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.58,1:02:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,what a thing is\NKorzybski of course
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.61,1:02:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Korzybski pointed out\Nthat the word is not the thing
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.61,1:02:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the map is not the territory\Nwhich led to the development of
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.61,1:02:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,along with Hayakawa\NProfessor Hayakawa from Hawaii
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.61,1:02:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,developed\Nwhat was the name of it now
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.96,1:03:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it was a whole movement\Nanyway they had a periodical called Etc
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.96,1:03:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and the point was to\Nbecome aware
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.96,1:03:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that verbalizations only exist\Nas a verbalization
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.96,1:03:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the fact that you can verbalize something\Ndoesn't mean it has a reality
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.96,1:03:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that's why there is no opposite\Nto truth
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.12,1:03:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that is one of the most profound things to learn\Nthe only thing that exists
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.40,1:03:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is truth\Nonly truth has existence
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.60,1:03:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,only that which has existence is truth\Nthat which is untruth has no existence
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.63,1:03:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so there is no point to fear it\Nbecause it has no existence
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.92,1:03:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it's something conjugal\Nconjured up
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.92,1:03:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,because we say\Nif there is a god there must be an anti-god
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.43,1:03:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,if there is good there must be evil\Nthis comes from a dualistic
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.26,1:03:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to reconstruct\Nthe dualistic universe for you today
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.42,1:04:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,but we ran out of time\Nthe definition
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.76,1:04:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the thinking that a thing exists\Nbecause there is a word
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.76,1:04:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is the fallibility of the ego\Nin the
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.76,1:04:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,level of the 400's\Nthat which has reality
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.80,1:04:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,has no opposite\Nthere is no opposite to god
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.80,1:04:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,oh I know how to define this\Nby really defining a kinesiologic response
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.60,1:04:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we said\Nconsciousness only knows truth
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.60,1:04:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't know falsehood\Nfalsehood has no existence
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.60,1:04:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,so how would it know it\Nconsequently if the statement you make
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.05,1:04:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,has truth it has existence\Nand consciousness recognizes
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.05,1:04:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,acknowledges existence\Nby making your arm go strong
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.05,1:04:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,say it has no tooth to it\Nit has no existence
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.05,1:04:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because it has no existence\Nit has no energy
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.05,1:04:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,it can't make your arm go strong\Nsay your arm goes weak
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.05,1:05:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,so all your arm is saying yes\Nor not yes
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.05,1:05:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that is different from yes from no\Nthis is a very profound and advanced understanding
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.53,1:05:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'll explain it in a way\Nthat you'll get it rather easily
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.01,1:05:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,in a wire\Neither electricity is on
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.97,1:05:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,or it's not on\Nthere is no condition known as offness
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.04,1:05:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you cannot turn on offness\Noffness has no reality
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.23,1:05:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,onness is either there\Nor it's not there
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.36,1:05:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the same with light and dark\Nthere is no such thing as darkness
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.64,1:05:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,except as a sensory observation\Nlight is either present
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.80,1:05:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,or not present\Nthere is no such thing
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.80,1:05:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,as an opposite to light\Nthere is no such thing as non-light
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.92,1:05:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,light is either present\Nor not present
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.69,1:05:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,if it's present strongly\Nit's brilliant
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.84,1:06:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,as it is less and less present\Nwe call that darkness
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.84,1:06:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,darkness is not the opposite\Nof light
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.29,1:06:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no such thing\Njust as offness does not exist
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.29,1:06:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,you can say that water is full of offness\Nit's not full of offness
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.29,1:06:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,it's only truth\Nand
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.45,1:06:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,because only the truth is real\Nthere is nothing to fear
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.55,1:06:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in the universe\Nyou see the nature of divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.55,1:06:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize\Nthere is nothing to fear in the universe
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.55,1:06:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,because divinity has no opposite\Nthe only thing
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.28,1:06:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that can grade\Ncan gradiate
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.28,1:06:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is your awareness of the divinity\Nof yourself and all of existence
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.28,1:06:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,so that the clouds\Nobscure the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.28,1:06:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but they are not the opposite of the sky\Nthe sky has no opposite
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.96,1:06:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no non-skyness\Nthat you have to fear
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.96,1:06:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no non-skyness\Nno
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.66,1:07:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,without the consciousness\Nof a Christ consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.04,1:07:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,then\Nbelow 200
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.04,1:07:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the darkness would be so obscure\None would never get to see the light of the sky
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.04,1:07:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore\Nwith help from others
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.33,1:07:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,from that consciousness\Nwe are lifted out of that darkness
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.50,1:07:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the difficulty\Nof what we are saying in kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.50,1:07:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,what kind of testing have you done\Nto rule out that a person's life view
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.50,1:07:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,or experience is not influencing the result\Nthe basic work out of which
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.50,1:07:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,power versus force came\Nwas
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.50,1:07:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,a dissertation presented to the university\Nand
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.50,1:07:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,well received by the university faculty\Ncalled
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.56,1:07:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,quantitative and qualitative analysis\Nand calibrations of the level of human consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.56,1:08:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,wow\Ncalibration
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.04,1:08:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I always forget it myself\Nanyway
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.04,1:08:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway\Nthat was a highly scientific
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.04,1:08:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,dissertation\Nin which we used traditional academic standards
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.04,1:08:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of\Nadvanced
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.48,1:08:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,statistical analysis\Nin fact I hired a statistical analysis firm
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.58,1:08:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,they took all the data\Nran it through their computers
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.58,1:08:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,P came out\NP was less than .001
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.58,1:08:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the chances of findings being\Nin error were less than 1 in 100,000
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.58,1:08:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,or something\Nalright so scientifically
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.32,1:08:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,those who are interested in it\Nit's available through the publisher of power versus force
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.32,1:08:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,called calibration and\Noh heck I'm not going to say it all again
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.41,1:08:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway\Nit has the scientific data
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.41,1:08:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,for those who like P is less than 1.001\Nand those kind of things
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.41,1:08:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,it's based on the null hypothesis\Nproving and disproving the null hypothesis
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.41,1:09:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,with valid data\Nso it met academic standards
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.41,1:09:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't have gotten a PhD for it\Nso
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.44,1:09:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,so that was the scientific validation\Nthe clinical
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.44,1:09:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a clinician rather than an academic\NI'm not an academic person at all
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.44,1:09:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a\Nclinical person
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.44,1:09:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritually I'm called a mystic I guess\Na mystic
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.44,1:09:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,how do you know the person's\Nexperience is not influencing
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.66,1:09:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you how to verify it for yourself\Nthere's two ways that are simple
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.66,1:09:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you can put information\Nyou can put a picture of
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.04,1:09:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Saddam Hussein\Nor somebody like that
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.04,1:09:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,or a mole discovered in the CIA\Nyou can put that in a envelope
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.04,1:09:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and give it to a child\Ntell the child hold this over your tummy
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.04,1:09:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and hold your arm out\Nand now you say this person's energy is positive
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.40,1:09:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the child doesn't know anything\Nabout what's in the envelope
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.40,1:10:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,he never heard of Saddam Hussein in the first place\Nso the child
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.40,1:10:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is the best demonstration for yourself\Nthat the child has no position on it
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.40,1:10:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't know\Nthe child has never heard of Saddam Hussein
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.40,1:10:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,or something\Nso you can use a child
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.40,1:10:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the innocence of the child\Nthe most powerful thing on this planet
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.55,1:10:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,is the innocent arm of the child\Nthe innocent arm of the child
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.03,1:10:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,tells the truth\Nor the falsehood
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.16,1:10:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,of anything in this universe\Nthat ever is or was
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.51,1:10:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,formidable\Nthe innocence of the child
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.51,1:10:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and his little arm out there\Ndefeat Hitler and Mussolini
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.51,1:10:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the terrible\Nbeings that are out there
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.80,1:10:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,live in dread of the innocence of the child\Nbecause it cannot be fooled
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.80,1:10:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the consciousness\Nis like the hardware
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.27,1:11:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and the ego is like the software\Nbut the hardware of a computer
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.27,1:11:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is uninfluenced\Nby the software you run through it
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.30,1:11:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the hardware is not influenced\Nby the programs you run through it
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.30,1:11:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it remains pristine\Nso consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.30,1:11:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,as a self\Nis intrinsically innocent
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.30,1:11:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and as you advance in consciousness\Nwhat you witness is the innocence
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.30,1:11:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of everyone around you\Nthat's why it's not possible
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.30,1:11:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to judge people anymore\Nit's not within the realm of reality
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.30,1:11:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you see that each person is\Nuniquely
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.30,1:11:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the innocent self\Nwhich then has gone unconscious
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.30,1:11:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and gotten programmed by all this software\Nand now this computer
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.30,1:11:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,thinks it's software\Nand it's forgotten that it's actually
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.30,1:11:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it's own hardware\Nto be enlightened
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.30,1:11:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,is to wipe out the software\Nand you realize
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.81,1:11:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,oh I was the hardware all along\Nthat's true
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.29,1:12:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,so anyway you can prove to yourself\Nthe nearest small child
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.29,1:12:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,who is innocent\Nand so you can have him
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.39,1:12:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,tell you what mankind\Nhas never been able to figure out
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.39,1:12:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the kinesiology\Nyou know the muscle test itself
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.39,1:12:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you should say\Nis this person good for me to work with
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.09,1:12:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,yes verify it\Nbecause sometimes spouses for some reason
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.09,1:12:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,do not work well together\NI haven't had time to research it
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.09,1:12:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I did research it one time\Nand I came up with an answer
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.12,1:12:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but I don't know what the answer was\Nit was like the secret of life
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.12,1:12:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned it on the way here today\NI was going to share it with you
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.12,1:12:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,jeez the minute I got\Nwhat the hell was it
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.12,1:12:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I know I knew what it was and I also realized\Nand it came back to me
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.40,1:12:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and I thought oh golly\NI've got to share that with the audience
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.40,1:12:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway\Nyou experiment
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.66,1:13:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,you say this person is good for me to work with\Nyes no
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.66,1:13:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,then you do the simple\Nyour subject holds love
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.88,1:13:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you hold something that's not love\Nand it's really very simple
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.88,1:13:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not really hard to do at all\Nvarious things may influence it
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.88,1:13:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and you'll find out what does\Nmusic in the background
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.88,1:13:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the environment\Nwhat are the other things that influence it
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.88,1:13:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,because she always\Nshe clears herself
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.88,1:13:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,don't look at anything close your eyes\Nyou saw that if you look at something
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.88,1:13:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that's like a smile you go strong\Nwhen you look at something that looks like a frown you go weak
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.92,1:13:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,just a visual image can influence it\Nso it takes a little practice
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.92,1:13:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a very good book\NYour Body Doesn't Lie by John Diamond
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.92,1:13:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it's also got another name\NBehavioral Kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.92,1:13:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it's been selling all these years\Na lot of paperback
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.92,1:13:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and that really goes into kinesiology\Nyou know for me
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.20,1:14:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,kinesiology was like the\Ntelescope to Galileo
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.20,1:14:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Galileo wasn't interested in telescopes\Nhe was interested in the universe
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.20,1:14:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,so I'm not really interested in kinesiology\Nexcept for its handiness
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.20,1:14:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,it's very handy and if you have somebody that you work well with\Nyou'll notice that
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.20,1:14:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,we very often in lectures\Nyou know we'll research something
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.20,1:14:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,right down the spot we've never asked before\Nlet's ask something right now
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.20,1:14:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the level of consciousness\Nof this lecture was over 600 resist
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.68,1:14:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,700 resist\N780 resist
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.68,1:14:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,750 resist\N760 resist
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.94,1:14:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the level of consciousness of this lecture itself\Nwhich I promised I would calibrate
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.94,1:14:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,is 750\N750 what it tells you is what level of truth that is
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.94,1:14:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what level\Nbecause truth is only truth
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.26,1:14:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,when defined in the context of its own level\Nwhat's truth on one level
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.26,1:14:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is falsehood on another\Ntruth is only true on its own level
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.26,1:14:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not true on other levels\Nand one of the great difficulties
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.26,1:15:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in spiritual and religious confusion\Nis the confusion of the levels
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.26,1:15:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,things are quoted\Nthat are applicable to one level
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.26,1:15:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and misapplied to another level\Nonward Christian soldiers
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.19,1:15:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't mean that you slaughter people\Nit means that
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.19,1:15:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the courage of Christ is within you\Nto face truth
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.19,1:15:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,so\Nmisinterpretation then comes from
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.38,1:15:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,mixing levels\Nquick mixing levels
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.41,1:15:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the spiritual warrior is not the same\Nas the killer warrior
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.41,1:15:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the killer warrior is a whole different trip\Nnow
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.02,1:15:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,there are various\Nthere are various ways of doing
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.02,1:15:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,this muscle testing\Nsome people have learned
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.02,1:15:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the ring method\Nyou hold a statement in mind
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.02,1:15:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,my name is George\Nmy name is David
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.02,1:16:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the circle goes strong\Nfalsehood makes it go weak
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.02,1:16:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,there are ways where you can squeeze your fingers together\Nso people have learned
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.02,1:16:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,different techniques\Nyou get intuitive about it yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.12,1:16:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,if you do this kind of testing\Nfor a period of time
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.12,1:16:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of truth versus falsehood\Nthe minute you state the question
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.18,1:16:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you already feel like a buzz\Nyou know what it is
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.18,1:16:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,like when I ask her a question\NI can almost feel what the buzz is going to be
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.18,1:16:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,she already feels the answer coming down\Nbefore her muscles react to it
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.18,1:16:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,she already feels it go through her consciousness\Nso that's
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.18,1:16:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,just bicycle riding\Nuntil you get really familiar with it
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.76,1:16:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,so there are those different techniques\NI once taught
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.79,1:16:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,my arm to be a pendulum\Nand false was this way I'd say
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.79,1:16:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I am my own grandfather\Nno I'm not my own grandfather
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.58,1:16:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I have two grandchildren\Nthat's a fact
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.56,1:17:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,so you see\Nthen I have people that say they feel they are going to fall over
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.56,1:17:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I have patients who are pretty\Nadvanced in consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.56,1:17:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the minute I hold a statement in my mind\Nif it's false I feel like
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.56,1:17:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to fall over\Nso everybody has these different ways
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.56,1:17:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's a sensitivity\Nthat you train yourself to observe
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.56,1:17:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,see most people take for granted\Nthe space in this room
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.56,1:17:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,most people take for granted\Ntheir own consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.56,1:17:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,awareness\Nnever aware that awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.79,1:17:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is a certain level of consciousness\Nthey just fear
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.79,1:17:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you always see your nose on your face\Nso people lose awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.97,1:17:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,of awareness itself\Nand they also confuse
